txt.en: Harvestmath brings yet another bountiful farming season to a close as the leaves begin to turn gold and the days grow short and cool.
Enjoy the autumn festivities while they last
The long summer has come to an end, and a beautiful autumn settles in over Middle-earth. The air grows crisper and cooler daily, and the sun retires earlier with each passing week.
The leaves have turned red and gold, and it would be wise to pick a warmer cloak when you leave your cozy house in the morning, for a gentle frost has settled upon the land.
